        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 5:34PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 534 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Orange, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newark, Jersey City, Elizabeth, Bayonne, Hoboken, Bloomfield, Linden,
Orange, Summit, Millburn, Secaucus, Harrison, Todt Hill, Caldwell,
and Port Richmond.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
